ImageStorage.js is a simple library for using PNG images as key value pair data holders

var imgStore = ImageStorage.loadFromURL("duck.png");

imgStore.set("foo","bar");
imgStore.get("foo");
imgStore.remove("blah");

imgStore.save(function(img){
    //do something with image with data
});

This might be useful in many ways, but be warned, many image hosting servers pngcrush/reduce/modify their image to remove useless data and improve size.